$interpreted: Sophie: Where's Tindoiimu!?
Hutchinson: We can't find her...
Ru-yi: There's so much snow, I can't see anything... Ah—a-choo!
Sophie: ...
Eidatyr: ...Looks like you lot won't stand a chance out here.
Sophie: Eidatyr...
Sophie: You couldn't find her either...
Eidatyr: Not even the locals dare to brave the snow out on this plain. You can forget about finding anyone out here once the blizzards come. Just be glad if you can keep from getting lost.
Sophie: What should we do? She's been separated from us for a while already... If we don't find her soon...
Eidatyr: Then we'll have no choice but to leave her. I told you already, this expedition was never gonna be a walk around the petting zoo.
Sophie: But...!
Hanbei: You up ahead, outta my waaaaaayyy!!
Ru-yi: Wh-wh-what!? Is it an avalanche? I'm not ready to die yet! Save me, Sophie!
Hutchinson: Wait a moment! This snowball looks rather familiar...
Hanbei: Gyagh! ...Owowow, that hurts like a—
Ru-yi: Huh? Hanbei?
Sophie: Hyaaah!
Eidatyr: He must have been attracted by all the commotion. Why not chuck a few snowballs into the mix?
Hanbei: It wasn't on purpose!
Eidatyr: Here I come!
Eidatyr: Tch, my fingers are frozen up...
Eidatyr: ...Aha... Ahahaha...
Sophie: Eidatyr?
Eidatyr: Haha... Oh, hell... I've been in Westport too long. I forgot how cold the true north really is...
Eidatyr: We'll perish long before we can find Tindoiimu if we stay out much longer in this snow. Let's look for shelter.
Sophie: Gwah... But...
Eidatyr: Come with me or don't, it's your life and your choice. But I don't plan on dying out here.
